{
  "texts": [
    "Along the same lines, previous research has shown that the public's reservations toward medical AI persist even when AI-generated content is medically supervised (18).",
    "Considering the expected surge of AI in healthcare and the immense potential for human-AI collaboration, this finding raises notable concerns.",
    "To address this bias, in addition to the general public, other stakeholders, such as physicians and insurance providers, will need to be engaged accordingly.",
    "Interestingly, another study showed that if people were assured that humans would remain unequivocally in the decision-making position, the combination of human and AI achieved significantly higher levels of trust than without this assurance (19).",
    "Consequently, the specific framing of AI's involvement in generating and delivering medical advice may be pivotal for its public acceptance."
  ]
}